channel.description:
Ok, before I get started I'd just like to say that I am not hosting this server, but am using it to improve my java "skills". I am just getting familiar with 667's. So I am new to 667's and I've tried my best to attempt a fix on these files extensions. For example if I go into the character folder it will have the user there like
random.p http://dl.dropbox.com/u/21446948/ggggggg.p
The source does have an Encoder and I was wondering If it had anything to do with that. There are also random file extensions like .e or .s just random extension that I've never seen. Also If anyone had any ideas or solutions please post, I've been looking all over the internet to fix this. When I try to open .p files with notepad or wordpad Its always encrypted for Example,
